{"title_page": "PlayStation All-Stars Island", "text_new": "{{Infobox video game\n|image         = \n|caption       = \n|developer     = [[Zoink]]\n|publisher     = [[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|designer      = \n|director      = \n|producer      = \n|writer        = \n|artist        = \n|composer      = \n|series        = \n|released      = {{vgrelease|EU|8 August 2013}}\n|genre         = [[Action game|Action]], [[endless runner]]\n|modes         = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n|platforms     = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]]\n}}\n\n'''''PlayStation All-Stars Island''''' is a [[free-to-play]] [[Fictional crossovers in video games|crossover video game]] featuring characters from various [[PlayStation]] franchises. The game was developed by [[Zoink]] and sponsored by [[Coke Zero]]. The game was announced, and released on August 8, 2013, and released in selected European territories; no North American release is planned.\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe game consists of four different game modes, each featuring a different character from a respective [[Sony Computer Entertainment]] video game franchise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vg247.com/2013/08/08/playstation-all-stars-island-heading-to-android-ios-and-sponsored-by-coke-zero/comment-page-1/ |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island heading to Android, iOS and sponsored by Coke Zero |publisher=VG247 |date=2008-01-28 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> This includes [[Nathan Drake (character)|Nathan Drake]] from ''[[Uncharted (series)|Uncharted]]'', [[Sackboy]] from ''[[LittleBigPlanet]]'', [[Cole MacGrath]] from ''[[Infamous (series)|Infamous]]'', and Kat from ''[[Gravity Rush]]''.<ref name=\"polygon89\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2013/8/9/4605498/playstation-all-stars-island-launch-trailer-teams-up-sackboy-and-nate |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island launch trailer teams up Sackboy and Nate Drake |publisher=Polygon |date=2013-08-01 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> The four mini-games all loosely play as [[endless runner]]s, though each have separate elements from their respective series as well; Nathan Drake runs through ancient ruins, Sack Boy races through levels similarly to ''[[LittleBigPlanet Karting]]'', and Kat retains her ability to shift gravity.<ref name=\"polygon89\"/>\n\nWithin the games, the player must direct the respective character through the game's [[level (video game)|levels]], avoiding obstacles and collecting [[Coca-Cola|Coke]]-themed items.<ref name=\"opm\">{{cite web |url=http://www.officialplaystationmagazine.co.uk/2013/08/09/playstation-all-stars-island-ios-thing/ |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island iOS & Android is an actual thing happening right now &#124; PS3 News |magazine=Official PlayStation Magazine |accessdate=2013-08-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JcueHas1?url=http://www.officialplaystationmagazine.co.uk/2013/08/09/playstation-all-stars-island-ios-thing/ |archivedate=2013-09-14 }}</ref> The collection of items unlocks further content, challenges, and even cameos from other PlayStation series such as [[Ratchet & Clank]], [[Jak and Daxter]], and Sackgirl.<ref>{{cite web|first=Mike |last=Jackson |url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/423480/coke-sponsored-playstation-all-stars-island-game-hits-smartphones/ |title=News: Coke-sponsored PlayStation All-Stars Island game hits smartphones |publisher=ComputerAndVideoGames.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> Additional game content may be downloaded by scanning [[QR code]]s on actual [[Coke Zero]] bottles.<ref name=\"opm\"/>\n\n==Development==\nThe game was announced on August 8, 2013, as a mobile phone game for [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] platforms, developed by [[Zoink]] and being sponsored by [[Coke Zero]].<ref name=\"gamespot1\">{{cite web|first=Martin |last=Gaston |url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/coca-cola-sponsored-playstation-all-stars-island-lands-on-mobile-6412701 |title=Coca-Cola sponsored PlayStation All-Stars Island lands on mobile |publisher=GameSpot.com |date=August 8, 2013 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref><ref name=\"ign1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/08/08/playstation-all-stars-gets-coke-sponsored-ios-android-app |title=PlayStation All-Stars Gets Coke-Sponsored iOS, Android App |publisher=IGN |date=2012-11-20 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> It was made available for download for its respective platforms on the same day as its announcement.<ref name=\"ign1\"/> The game was released in select European territories; Sony has announced there are no plans for the game to be released in North America.<ref name=\"ign1\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nThe game has been compared unfavorably to ''[[Halo 4#Marketing|Halo 4: King of the Hill Refueled by Mountain Dew]]''<ref name=\"gamespot1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://toucharcade.com/2013/08/08/sony-launches-playstation-all-stars-island-promotional-game-portal-in-the-uk/ |title=Sony Launches 'PlayStation All-Stars Island' Promotional Game Portal in the UK |publisher=Touch Arcade |date=2011-11-29 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> as an example of excessive and blatant advertising in a video game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.destructoid.com/playstation-all-stars-island-wants-you-to-drink-coke-zero-259653.phtml |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island wants you to drink Coke Zero |publisher=Destructoid |date= |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> ''[[The Escapist (magazine)|The Escapist]]'' criticized the advertising as being \"obnoxious\", complaining of an unfavorable Coke-to-Sony representation in the game, with there being more Coke ads than Sony characters.<ref>{{cite web|first=Earnest | last=Cavalli |url=http://www.escapistmagazine.com/news/view/126719-PlayStation-All-Stars-Island-Wears-Endorsements-On-Its-Sleeve |title=The Escapist : News : PlayStation All-Stars Island Wears Endorsements On Its Sleeve |publisher=Escapistmagazine.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*''[[PlayStation All-Stars Battle Royale]]'', a 2012 fighting game that combines PlayStation-related characters in a similar manner\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2013 video games]]\n[[Category:Action video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:Crossover video games]]\n[[Category:Sony Interactive Entertainment games]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Endless runner games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Advergames]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox video game\n|image         = \n|caption       = \n|developer     = [[Zoink]]\n|publisher     = [[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|designer      = \n|director      = \n|producer      = \n|writer        = \n|artist        = \n|composer      = \n|series        = \n|released      = {{vgrelease|EU|8 August 2013}}\n|genre         = [[Action game|Action]], [[endless runner]]\n|modes         = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n|platforms     = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]]\n}}\n\n'''''PlayStation All-Stars Island''''' is a [[free-to-play]] [[Fictional crossovers in video games|crossover video game]] featuring characters from various [[PlayStation]] franchises. The game was developed by [[Zoink]] and sponsored by [[Coke Zero]]. The game was announced, and released on August 8, 2013, and released in selected European territories; no North American release is planned.\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe game consists of four different game modes, each featuring a different character from a respective [[Sony Computer Entertainment]] video game franchise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vg247.com/2013/08/08/playstation-all-stars-island-heading-to-android-ios-and-sponsored-by-coke-zero/comment-page-1/ |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island heading to Android, iOS and sponsored by Coke Zero |publisher=VG247 |date=2008-01-28 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> This includes [[Nathan Drake (character)|Nathan Drake]] from ''[[Uncharted (series)|Uncharted]]'', [[Sackboy]] from ''[[LittleBigPlanet]]'', [[Cole MacGrath]] from ''[[Infamous (series)|Infamous]]'', and Kat from ''[[Gravity Rush]]''.<ref name=\"polygon89\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2013/8/9/4605498/playstation-all-stars-island-launch-trailer-teams-up-sackboy-and-nate |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island launch trailer teams up Sackboy and Nate Drake |publisher=Polygon |date=2013-08-01 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> The four mini-games all loosely play as [[endless runner]]s, though each have separate elements from their respective series as well; Nathan Drake runs though ancient ruins, Sack Boy races through levels similarly to ''[[LittleBigPlanet Karting]]'', and Kat retains her ability to shift gravity.<ref name=\"polygon89\"/>\n\nWithin the games, the player must direct the respective character through the game's [[level (video game)|levels]], avoiding obstacles and collecting [[Coca-Cola|Coke]]-themed items.<ref name=\"opm\">{{cite web |url=http://www.officialplaystationmagazine.co.uk/2013/08/09/playstation-all-stars-island-ios-thing/ |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island iOS & Android is an actual thing happening right now &#124; PS3 News |magazine=Official PlayStation Magazine |accessdate=2013-08-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JcueHas1?url=http://www.officialplaystationmagazine.co.uk/2013/08/09/playstation-all-stars-island-ios-thing/ |archivedate=2013-09-14 }}</ref> The collection of items unlocks further content, challenges, and even cameos from other PlayStation series such as [[Ratchet & Clank]], [[Jak and Daxter]], and Sackgirl.<ref>{{cite web|first=Mike |last=Jackson |url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/423480/coke-sponsored-playstation-all-stars-island-game-hits-smartphones/ |title=News: Coke-sponsored PlayStation All-Stars Island game hits smartphones |publisher=ComputerAndVideoGames.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> Additional game content may be downloaded by scanning [[QR code]]s on actual [[Coke Zero]] bottles.<ref name=\"opm\"/>\n\n==Development==\nThe game was announced on August 8, 2013, as a mobile phone game for [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] platforms, developed by [[Zoink]] and being sponsored by [[Coke Zero]].<ref name=\"gamespot1\">{{cite web|first=Martin |last=Gaston |url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/coca-cola-sponsored-playstation-all-stars-island-lands-on-mobile-6412701 |title=Coca-Cola sponsored PlayStation All-Stars Island lands on mobile |publisher=GameSpot.com |date=August 8, 2013 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref><ref name=\"ign1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/08/08/playstation-all-stars-gets-coke-sponsored-ios-android-app |title=PlayStation All-Stars Gets Coke-Sponsored iOS, Android App |publisher=IGN |date=2012-11-20 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> It was made available for download for its respective platforms on the same day as its announcement.<ref name=\"ign1\"/> The game was released in select European territories; Sony has announced there are no plans for the game to be released in North America.<ref name=\"ign1\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nThe game has been compared unfavorably to ''[[Halo 4#Marketing|Halo 4: King of the Hill Refueled by Mountain Dew]]''<ref name=\"gamespot1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://toucharcade.com/2013/08/08/sony-launches-playstation-all-stars-island-promotional-game-portal-in-the-uk/ |title=Sony Launches 'PlayStation All-Stars Island' Promotional Game Portal in the UK |publisher=Touch Arcade |date=2011-11-29 |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> as an example of excessive and blatant advertising in a video game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.destructoid.com/playstation-all-stars-island-wants-you-to-drink-coke-zero-259653.phtml |title=PlayStation All-Stars Island wants you to drink Coke Zero |publisher=Destructoid |date= |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref> ''[[The Escapist (magazine)|The Escapist]]'' criticized the advertising as being \"obnoxious\", complaining of an unfavorable Coke-to-Sony representation in the game, with there being more Coke ads than Sony characters.<ref>{{cite web|first=Earnest | last=Cavalli |url=http://www.escapistmagazine.com/news/view/126719-PlayStation-All-Stars-Island-Wears-Endorsements-On-Its-Sleeve |title=The Escapist : News : PlayStation All-Stars Island Wears Endorsements On Its Sleeve |publisher=Escapistmagazine.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-09}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*''[[PlayStation All-Stars Battle Royale]]'', a 2012 fighting game that combines PlayStation-related characters in a similar manner\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2013 video games]]\n[[Category:Action video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:Crossover video games]]\n[[Category:Sony Interactive Entertainment games]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Endless runner games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Advergames]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGameplay:Typo fixing, replaced: runs though  \u2192  runs through", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PlayStation_All-Stars_Island"}
{"title_page": "Appayya (2013 film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n|name            = Appayya\n| image          = Appayya_(2013_film).jpg\n|director        = [[S. Narayan]]\n|producer        = Bhagyavathi Narayan<br>[[S. Narayan]]\n|starring        = [[Srinagar Kitty]]<br>[[Surabhi Prabhu]]<br>[[Bhama]]\n|music           = [[S. Narayan]]<br>Dharma Vish (background score)\n|cinematography  = Jagadish Wali\n|choreography    = \n|released        = {{Film date|df=yes|2013|09|13|ref=1<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/kannada/article/97426.html|title=2 Films for 2 Days!|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=13 September 2013}}</ref>}}\n|studio          = Bhagyavathi Combines\n|editing         = \n|language        = Kannada\n|country         = India\n|budget          = \n}}\n\n'''''Appayya''''' ({{lang-kan|\u0c85\u0caa\u0ccd\u0caa\u0caf\u0ccd\u0caf}}) is a 2013 Kannada romance film written, directed and co-produced by [[S. Narayan]]. He has also scored the music for the film.  It is produced under Bhagyavathi Combines. [[Srinagar Kitty]] and [[Bhama]] are in the lead roles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.supergoodmovies.com/44122/sandalwood/appayya-all-set-for-june-release-news-details|title='Appayya' all Set for June Release|date=4 May 2012|accessdate=9 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120507024502/http://www.supergoodmovies.com/44122/sandalwood/appayya-all-set-for-june-release-news-details|archive-date=7 May 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> All songs have been arranged and programmed by Dharma Vish who has also composed the background music.\n\n\"Bombayalli Galli Galli\" song was shot featuring [[supermodel]] & [[actress]] [[Surabhi Prabhu]]<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/movie-details/news-interviews/Surabhi-turns-an-item-girl/articleshow/11616506.cms?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=iOSapp</ref> , <ref>https://kannada.webdunia.com/kannada-cinema-news/%E0%B2%95%E0%B2%A8%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%A8%E0%B2%A1%E0%B2%95%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%95%E0%B2%BE%E0%B2%97%E0%B2%BF-%E0%B2%95%E0%B2%BF%E0%B2%9F%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%9F%E0%B2%BF-%E0%B2%9C%E0%B2%A4%E0%B3%86-%E0%B2%B8%E0%B3%81%E0%B2%B0%E0%B2%AD%E0%B2%BF-%E0%B2%90%E0%B2%9F%E0%B2%82-%E0%B2%A1%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%AF%E0%B2%BE%E0%B2%A8%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%B8%E0%B3%8D-112012700028_1.htm</ref>\u00a0.\nAfter much delay in finding the release date, the film finally made its premier across Karnataka on 13 September 2013.<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/kannada/article/97426.html 2 Films for 2 Days!]</ref> It was remade in [[Cinema of Bangladesh|Bangladeshi]] in 2016 as ''[[Angaar (2016 film)|Angaar]]'' starring with [[Om (actor)|Om]] and [[Falguni Rahman Jolly|Jolly]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://moviepagla.com/archives/1977|title=\u0985\u09a8\u09b2\u09be\u0987\u09a8\u09c7 \u2018\u0985\u0999\u09cd\u0997\u09be\u09b0\u2019 \u099b\u09ac\u09bf\u09b0 \u09ab\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09b8\u09cd\u099f \u09b2\u09c1\u0995 \u099f\u09bf\u099c\u09be\u09b0 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u0995\u09be\u09b6 (\u09ad\u09bf\u09a1\u09bf\u0993 \u09b8\u09b9)|last=Mridul|first=Ahmed|date=14 November 2015|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> thereby becoming the third Kannada film to be remade in Bangladeshi as well as the third Kannada movie to be remade in a foreign language after ''[[Anuraga Aralithu]]'' and ''[[Appu (2002 film)|Appu]]''.\n\n==Production==\n''Appayya'' for which he procured the story from a stranger in Bengaluru International airport by paying Rs.25000 stars Srinagara Kitty in the lead role with Bhama as counterpart. This is the real-life story completing shooting has finished the re-recording at sounDsiesigns Recording studio by Dharma Vish.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Srinagar Kitty]] as Appayya\n*[[Surabhi Prabhu]]\n*[[Bhama]] \n*Indrakumar\n \n*Suresh Chandra\n*Asha Rani\n*[[S. Narayan]]\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Appayya\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[S. Narayan]]\n| cover   