{"title_page": "Xia Da", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{short description|Chinese comics artist}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Xia (surname)|Xia]]}}\n{{Infobox comics creator\n| name_nonEN = \u590f\u8fbe\n| nonUS = \n| image = 2016TIBE_Day5_Hall1_Xia_Da.jpg\n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = Xia Da in 2016\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1981|04|04}}\n| birth_place = [[Huaihua]], [[Hunan]], China.\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = Chinese\n| nationality2 = \n| area = Manhua artist\n| alias = \n| notable works = Zi Bu Yu, Chang Ge Xing\n| collaborators = \n| awards = [[Golden Dragon Award]], [[Golden Monkey Award]]\n| spouse = \n| children = \n| relatives = \n| signature = \n| signature_alt = \n| module = \n| website = \n| bodyclass = \n}}\n'''Xia Da''' ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}}; born 4 April 1981) is a [[Chinese People|Chinese]] [[manhua]] artist.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://culture.ifeng.com/gundong/detail_2011_02/14/4652868_0.shtml|title=\u590f\u8fbe\uff1a\u53ea\u6709\u5bf9\u7740\u767d\u7eb8\u7684\u65f6\u5019\uff0c\u624d\u4f1a\u89c9\u5f97\u81ea\u5728_\u6587\u5316\u9891\u9053_\u51e4\u51f0\u7f51|website=culture.ifeng.com|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u590f\u8fbe\uff0c1981\u5e744\u67084\u65e5\u51fa\u751f\u4e8e\u6e56\u5357\u6000\u5316\u3002}}</ref> She is best known for creating the comics ''Zi Bu Yu'' and ''Chang Ge Xing'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://epaper.xkb.com.cn/view/1139263|title=\"\u4e2d\u56fd\u98ce\"\u662f\u57fa\u56e0 \u662f\u52a8\u6f2b\u56de\u5f52\u81ea\u6211\u7684\u94a5\u5319-\u5e7f\u4e1c\u65b0\u5feb\u7f51-\u65b0\u5feb\u62a5\u5b98\u65b9\u7f51\u7ad9(\u660e\u5929\u62a5\u7eb8\u4eca\u665a\u770b\u00b7\u80fd\u89c1\u62a5\u7684\u535a\u5ba2\u00b7\u4eba\u4eba\u505a\u8bb0\u8005)|website=epaper.xkb.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u53e6\u5982\u590f\u8fbe\u7684\u300a\u957f\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u300a\u5b50\u4e0d\u8bed\u300b\u4e5f\u5f88\u53d7\u6b22\u8fce\u3002\u8fd9\u4e00\u6279\u76f8\u5f53\u4f18\u79c0\u7684\u4f5c\u8005,\u6709\u4e86\u4e00\u79cd\u4e3b\u52a8\u7684\u8ba4\u8bc6,\u8981\u521b\u4f5c\u51fa\u4ee3\u8868\u6211\u4eec\u81ea\u5df1\u6587\u5316\u7279\u8272\u7684\u4f5c\u54c1\u3002}}</ref> and five million copies of her works have been sold as of 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ori.hangzhou.com.cn/ornews/content/2018-08/11/content_7050576.htm|title=\u63a2\u8bbf\u590f\u8fbe\u5de5\u4f5c\u5ba4\u2014\u2014\u9e9f\u8dbe\u5c45 \u5e26\u4f60\u8d70\u8fd1\u8fd9\u6837\u7684\u590f\u8fbe - \u676d\u7f51\u539f\u521b - \u676d\u5dde\u7f51|website=ori.hangzhou.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u590f\u8fbe\u6f2b\u753b\u8fde\u8f7d\u4f5c\u54c1\u957f\u671f\u8986\u76d6\u5168\u56fd\u5404\u5927\u4e3b\u6d41\u6f2b\u753b\u5e73\u53f0,\u5355\u884c\u672c\u9500\u552e\u65e9\u8d85\u8fc7500\u4e07\u518c\uff0c\u62e5\u6709\u57fa\u6570\u5e9e\u5927\u7684\u7c89\u4e1d\u7fa4\u4f53\u957f\u671f\u5173\u6ce8\uff0c\u7c89\u4e1d\u6548\u5e94\u8986\u76d6\u5168\u56fd\u548c\u5168\u7403\u534e\u4eba\u533a\u57df\u3002}}</ref> Her art has been noted for its [[Chinese art|classical]] style, and have been met with positive reception in both China and Japan.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20141101001020-260306?chdtv|title=\u6f2b\u756b\u7db2\u8def\u5e36\u52d5\u71b1\u6f6e \u5c55\u73fe\u4e2d\u570b\u7f8e\u5b78 - \u5169\u5cb8\u85dd\u6587|last=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|website=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|language=zh-Hant-TW|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nXia Da was born on 4 April 1981, in [[Huaihua|Huaihua, Hunan]].<ref name=\":1\" /> Her interests had included painting and comic-reading since she was a child, and she was eventually inspired to make her own comics in high school. She published her first work, titled ''Cheng Zhang'', in the ''[[Beijing Cartoon]]'' magazine, receiving an encouraging, handwritten reply by her editorial teacher. After graduating from university, she moved to [[Beijing]] and briefly worked in advertising before quitting to focus on her own comics. During this time, she became engrossed in drawing, seldom leaving her apartment as she lived on a modest income.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\n[[File:Hangzhou Library 33.jpg|left|thumb|Panels of Chang Ge Xing shown in the [[Hangzhou Library]]|235x235px]]\nHer first comic book, ''April Story'', was published in 2003 shortly before her college graduation.{{sfn|Ogi|Suter|Lent|2019|p=248}} ''Zi Bu Yu'', her second work, was serialized in 2008. The series won the 5th [[Golden Dragon Award]] on the same year, and was subsequently published in Japan by [[Ultra Jump]] in 2009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://paper.people.com.cn/rmrbhwb/html/2010-05/19/content_520931.htm?div=-1|title=\u4eba\u6c11\u65e5\u62a5\u6d77\u5916\u7248-\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51|website=paper.people.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref> Prior to its publication in Japan, the work was reviewed and recommended by Matsui Sakamoto, editor-in-chief of the manga [[Saint Seiya]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cul.sohu.com/20090925/n267001201.shtml|title=\u5b50\u4e0d\u8bed\u4ecb\u7ecd-\u641c\u72d0\u6587\u5316\u9891\u9053|website=cul.sohu.com|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u53d7\u65e5\u672c\u96c6\u82f1\u793e\u603b\u7f16\u8f91\u957f\u8302\u6728\u884c\u96c4\u548c\u8457\u540d\u6f2b\u753b\u7f16\u8f91\u677e\u4e95\u8363\u5143\uff08\u4ee3\u8868\u4f5c\uff1a\u5723\u6597\u58eb\u661f\u77e2\uff09\u7684\u5927\u529b\u63a8\u8350}}</ref>\n\nAfter the release of ''Zi Bu Yu'', Xia Da published several other comics. ''Chang Ge Xing'', a [[Historical period drama|historical drama]] set in the [[Tang dynasty|Tang Dynasty]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20160221000355-260115?chdtv|title=\u590f\u9054\u9577\u6b4c\u884c \u300c\u9084\u6c92\u958b\u59cb\u4e0b\u91cd\u624b\u300d - \u85dd\u6587\u526f\u520a|last=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|website=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|language=zh-Hant-TW|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref> received the Golden Monkey Award for Chinese Comics during its serialization,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/0/65420.html|title=\u53f0\u7063\u6f2b\u756b\u5bb6 T.K \u7ae0\u4e16\u7098\u300a\u9ed1\u8272\u72c2\u60f3\u66f2\u300b\u65bc\u4e2d\u570b 2012\u300c\u91d1\u7334\u734e\u300d\u7372\u734e|website=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u4e2d\u570b\u6f2b\u756b\u5927\u734e\uff1a\u300a\u9577\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u590f\u5929\u5cf6\u5f71\u8996\u52d5\u6f2b\u5236\u4f5c\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\uff08\u4f5c\u8005\uff1a\u590f\u9054\uff09}}</ref> and a televised series based on the comic began shooting in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/0/176540.html|title=\u590f\u9054\u6f2b\u756b\u300a\u9577\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u5c07\u63a8\u51fa\u771f\u4eba\u96fb\u8996\u5287 \u9810\u8a08\u5c07\u65bc\u4eca\u5e74 8 \u6708\u958b\u62cd|website=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2016, Xia Da issued an article on [[Sina Weibo|Weibo]] holding Summer Island Studio responsible for an unequal contract agreement set to last for 10 years. A publication hiatus for ''Chang Ge Xing'' was announced in the same article, with Xia Da citing issues with her health as the main cause.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ccnovel.com/103518_2.html|title=\u300a\u957f\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u4f5c\u8005\u590f\u8fbe\u79f0\u81ea\u5df1\"\u53d7\u591f\u4e86\" \u5979\u906d\u9047\u4e86\u5565\uff1f--\u897f\u8bfa\u7f51|website=www.ccnovel.com|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref> On 26 December, Xia Da and more than 30 comic creators announced their contract withdrawal from Summer Island.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://finance.sina.com.cn/roll/2018-08-27/doc-ihifuvph8314442.shtml|title=\u6f2b\u753b\u5de5\u4f5c\u5ba4\u590f\u5929\u5c9b\u89e3\u7ea6\u7ea0\u7eb7\u518d\u8d77|last=\u5317\u4eac\u5546\u62a5|date=2018-08-27|website=finance.sina.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, Xia Da announced the formation of her own studio in [[Hangzhou]], along with the serialization of a new comic, ''Shiyi Liu''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zjnews.zjol.com.cn/zjnews/hznews/201709/t20170928_5229099_ext.shtml|title=\u4e13\u8bbf\u521a\u590d\u51fa\u7684\u590f\u8fbe\u2014\u2014\u86f0\u4f0f\u534a\u5e74\uff0c\u592a\u60f3\u75db\u5feb\u753b\u4e00\u628a_\u624b\u673a\u6d59\u6c5f\u7f51|website=zjnews.zjol.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nXia Da has won many awards including:\n*Golden Dragon Award for Best Girls' comic{{sfn|Ogi|Suter|Lent|2019|p=248}}\n*Newcomer Award at the first Sino-Japanese Youth Exchange Cartoon Festival{{sfn|Ogi|Suter|Lent|2019|p=248}}\n\n== Bibliography == \n* ''Winter Fairy Tale'' (2002)\n* {{cite book |ref=harv|last=Da|first=Xia ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}})| authorlink =Xia Da| title = \u56db\u6708\u7269\u8bed/: \u590f\u8fbe\u4f18\u79c0\u6f2b\u753b\u77ed\u7bc7\u96c6|trans-title=April Story|year=2004| publisher = \u7535\u5b50\u5de5\u4e1a\u51fa\u7248\u793e| isbn= 9787505398962|language=Chinese}} <small>- Total pages: 174 </small> \n* {{cite book |ref=harv|last=Da|first=Xia ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}})| authorlink =Xia Da| title =\u6e38\u56ed\u60ca\u68a6|trans-title=|year=2008| publisher = \u6e56\u5357\u5c11\u5e74\u513f\u7ae5\u51fa\u7248\u793e| isbn= 9787535838858|language=Chinese}} <small>- Total pages: 85 </small>  \n* ''Peony Pavilion'' (2008)\n* ''Zi Bu Yu'' #1\u20132 (2008)\n* ''Tonglei'' (2009)\n* ''Morning Star of Midland'' (2009)\n* {{cite book |ref=harv|last=Da|first=Xia ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}})| authorlink =Xia Da| title =\u54e5\u65af\u62c9\u4e0d\u8bf4\u8bdd|trans-title=Godzilla Never Speaks|year=2010| publisher =\u65b0\u4e16\u7eaa\u51fa\u7248\u793e\u793e| isbn= 9787540544508|language=Chinese}} <small>- Total pages: 120 </small> \n* ''Chuxia'' (paintings) (2011)\n* ''Chang Ge Xing'' #1\u20136 (2012\u20132014) {{ISBN|9789571363233}}\n* ''Shiyi Liu'' (2018)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n*{{cite book |ref=harv|last=Ogi|first=Fusami |last2=Suter|first2=Rebecca |last3=Lent|first3=John A. | title = Women's Manga in Asia and Beyond: Uniting Different Cultures and Identities|year=2019| publisher = [[Springer Publishing|Springer]]| isbn= 9783319972299}} <small>- Total pages: 366 </small>\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Xia, Da}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chinese comics artists]]\n[[Category:People from Huaihua]]\n[[Category:Artists from Hunan]]\n[[Category:21st-century Chinese artists]]\n[[Category:Chinese female comics artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{short description|Chinese comics artist}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Xia (surname)|Xia]]}}\n{{Infobox comics creator\n| name = Xia Da\n| name_nonEN = \u590f\u8fbe\n| nonUS = \n| image = 2016TIBE_Day5_Hall1_Xia_Da.jpg\n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = Xia Da in 2016\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1981|04|04}}\n| birth_place = [[Huaihua]], [[Hunan]], China.\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = Chinese\n| nationality2 = \n| area = Manhua artist\n| alias = \n| notable works = Zi Bu Yu, Chang Ge Xing\n| collaborators = \n| awards = [[Golden Dragon Award]], [[Golden Monkey Award]]\n| spouse = \n| children = \n| relatives = \n| signature = \n| signature_alt = \n| module = \n| website = \n| bodyclass = \n}}\n'''Xia Da''' ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}}; born 4 April 1981) is a [[Chinese People|Chinese]] [[manhua]] artist.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://culture.ifeng.com/gundong/detail_2011_02/14/4652868_0.shtml|title=\u590f\u8fbe\uff1a\u53ea\u6709\u5bf9\u7740\u767d\u7eb8\u7684\u65f6\u5019\uff0c\u624d\u4f1a\u89c9\u5f97\u81ea\u5728_\u6587\u5316\u9891\u9053_\u51e4\u51f0\u7f51|website=culture.ifeng.com|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u590f\u8fbe\uff0c1981\u5e744\u67084\u65e5\u51fa\u751f\u4e8e\u6e56\u5357\u6000\u5316\u3002}}</ref> She is best known for creating the comics ''Zi Bu Yu'' and ''Chang Ge Xing'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://epaper.xkb.com.cn/view/1139263|title=\"\u4e2d\u56fd\u98ce\"\u662f\u57fa\u56e0 \u662f\u52a8\u6f2b\u56de\u5f52\u81ea\u6211\u7684\u94a5\u5319-\u5e7f\u4e1c\u65b0\u5feb\u7f51-\u65b0\u5feb\u62a5\u5b98\u65b9\u7f51\u7ad9(\u660e\u5929\u62a5\u7eb8\u4eca\u665a\u770b\u00b7\u80fd\u89c1\u62a5\u7684\u535a\u5ba2\u00b7\u4eba\u4eba\u505a\u8bb0\u8005)|website=epaper.xkb.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u53e6\u5982\u590f\u8fbe\u7684\u300a\u957f\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u300a\u5b50\u4e0d\u8bed\u300b\u4e5f\u5f88\u53d7\u6b22\u8fce\u3002\u8fd9\u4e00\u6279\u76f8\u5f53\u4f18\u79c0\u7684\u4f5c\u8005,\u6709\u4e86\u4e00\u79cd\u4e3b\u52a8\u7684\u8ba4\u8bc6,\u8981\u521b\u4f5c\u51fa\u4ee3\u8868\u6211\u4eec\u81ea\u5df1\u6587\u5316\u7279\u8272\u7684\u4f5c\u54c1\u3002}}</ref> and five million copies of her works have been sold as of 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ori.hangzhou.com.cn/ornews/content/2018-08/11/content_7050576.htm|title=\u63a2\u8bbf\u590f\u8fbe\u5de5\u4f5c\u5ba4\u2014\u2014\u9e9f\u8dbe\u5c45 \u5e26\u4f60\u8d70\u8fd1\u8fd9\u6837\u7684\u590f\u8fbe - \u676d\u7f51\u539f\u521b - \u676d\u5dde\u7f51|website=ori.hangzhou.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u590f\u8fbe\u6f2b\u753b\u8fde\u8f7d\u4f5c\u54c1\u957f\u671f\u8986\u76d6\u5168\u56fd\u5404\u5927\u4e3b\u6d41\u6f2b\u753b\u5e73\u53f0,\u5355\u884c\u672c\u9500\u552e\u65e9\u8d85\u8fc7500\u4e07\u518c\uff0c\u62e5\u6709\u57fa\u6570\u5e9e\u5927\u7684\u7c89\u4e1d\u7fa4\u4f53\u957f\u671f\u5173\u6ce8\uff0c\u7c89\u4e1d\u6548\u5e94\u8986\u76d6\u5168\u56fd\u548c\u5168\u7403\u534e\u4eba\u533a\u57df\u3002}}</ref> Her art has been noted for its [[Chinese art|classical]] style, and have been met with positive reception in both China and Japan.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20141101001020-260306?chdtv|title=\u6f2b\u756b\u7db2\u8def\u5e36\u52d5\u71b1\u6f6e \u5c55\u73fe\u4e2d\u570b\u7f8e\u5b78 - \u5169\u5cb8\u85dd\u6587|last=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|website=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|language=zh-Hant-TW|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nXia Da was born on 4 April 1981, in [[Huaihua|Huaihua, Hunan]].<ref name=\":1\" /> Her interests had included painting and comic-reading since she was a child, and she was eventually inspired to make her own comics in high school. She published her first work, titled ''Cheng Zhang'', in the ''[[Beijing Cartoon]]'' magazine, receiving an encouraging, handwritten reply by her editorial teacher. After graduating from university, she moved to [[Beijing]] and briefly worked in advertising before quitting to focus on her own comics. During this time, she became engrossed in drawing, seldom leaving her apartment as she lived on a modest income.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Career ==\n[[File:Hangzhou Library 33.jpg|left|thumb|Panels of Chang Ge Xing shown in the [[Hangzhou Library]]|235x235px]]\nHer first comic book, ''April Story'', was published in 2003 shortly before her college graduation.{{sfn|Ogi|Suter|Lent|2019|p=248}} ''Zi Bu Yu'', her second work, was serialized in 2008. The series won the 5th [[Golden Dragon Award]] on the same year, and was subsequently published in Japan by [[Ultra Jump]] in 2009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://paper.people.com.cn/rmrbhwb/html/2010-05/19/content_520931.htm?div=-1|title=\u4eba\u6c11\u65e5\u62a5\u6d77\u5916\u7248-\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51|website=paper.people.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref> Prior to its publication in Japan, the work was reviewed and recommended by Matsui Sakamoto, editor-in-chief of the manga [[Saint Seiya]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cul.sohu.com/20090925/n267001201.shtml|title=\u5b50\u4e0d\u8bed\u4ecb\u7ecd-\u641c\u72d0\u6587\u5316\u9891\u9053|website=cul.sohu.com|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u53d7\u65e5\u672c\u96c6\u82f1\u793e\u603b\u7f16\u8f91\u957f\u8302\u6728\u884c\u96c4\u548c\u8457\u540d\u6f2b\u753b\u7f16\u8f91\u677e\u4e95\u8363\u5143\uff08\u4ee3\u8868\u4f5c\uff1a\u5723\u6597\u58eb\u661f\u77e2\uff09\u7684\u5927\u529b\u63a8\u8350}}</ref>\n\nAfter the release of ''Zi Bu Yu'', Xia Da published several other comics. ''Chang Ge Xing'', a [[Historical period drama|historical drama]] set in the [[Tang dynasty|Tang Dynasty]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinatimes.com/newspapers/20160221000355-260115?chdtv|title=\u590f\u9054\u9577\u6b4c\u884c \u300c\u9084\u6c92\u958b\u59cb\u4e0b\u91cd\u624b\u300d - \u85dd\u6587\u526f\u520a|last=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|website=\u4e2d\u6642\u96fb\u5b50\u5831|language=zh-Hant-TW|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref> received the Golden Monkey Award for Chinese Comics during its serialization,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/0/65420.html|title=\u53f0\u7063\u6f2b\u756b\u5bb6 T.K \u7ae0\u4e16\u7098\u300a\u9ed1\u8272\u72c2\u60f3\u66f2\u300b\u65bc\u4e2d\u570b 2012\u300c\u91d1\u7334\u734e\u300d\u7372\u734e|website=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9|access-date=2019-06-09|quote=\u4e2d\u570b\u6f2b\u756b\u5927\u734e\uff1a\u300a\u9577\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u590f\u5929\u5cf6\u5f71\u8996\u52d5\u6f2b\u5236\u4f5c\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\uff08\u4f5c\u8005\uff1a\u590f\u9054\uff09}}</ref> and a televised series based on the comic began shooting in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/0/176540.html|title=\u590f\u9054\u6f2b\u756b\u300a\u9577\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u5c07\u63a8\u51fa\u771f\u4eba\u96fb\u8996\u5287 \u9810\u8a08\u5c07\u65bc\u4eca\u5e74 8 \u6708\u958b\u62cd|website=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2016, Xia Da issued an article on [[Sina Weibo|Weibo]] holding Summer Island Studio responsible for an unequal contract agreement set to last for 10 years. A publication hiatus for ''Chang Ge Xing'' was announced in the same article, with Xia Da citing issues with her health as the main cause.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ccnovel.com/103518_2.html|title=\u300a\u957f\u6b4c\u884c\u300b\u4f5c\u8005\u590f\u8fbe\u79f0\u81ea\u5df1\"\u53d7\u591f\u4e86\" \u5979\u906d\u9047\u4e86\u5565\uff1f--\u897f\u8bfa\u7f51|website=www.ccnovel.com|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref> On 26 December, Xia Da and more than 30 comic creators announced their contract withdrawal from Summer Island.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://finance.sina.com.cn/roll/2018-08-27/doc-ihifuvph8314442.shtml|title=\u6f2b\u753b\u5de5\u4f5c\u5ba4\u590f\u5929\u5c9b\u89e3\u7ea6\u7ea0\u7eb7\u518d\u8d77|last=\u5317\u4eac\u5546\u62a5|date=2018-08-27|website=finance.sina.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, Xia Da announced the formation of her own studio in [[Hangzhou]], along with the serialization of a new comic, ''Shiyi Liu''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zjnews.zjol.com.cn/zjnews/hznews/201709/t20170928_5229099_ext.shtml|title=\u4e13\u8bbf\u521a\u590d\u51fa\u7684\u590f\u8fbe\u2014\u2014\u86f0\u4f0f\u534a\u5e74\uff0c\u592a\u60f3\u75db\u5feb\u753b\u4e00\u628a_\u624b\u673a\u6d59\u6c5f\u7f51|website=zjnews.zjol.com.cn|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nXia Da has won many awards including:\n*Golden Dragon Award for Best Girls' comic{{sfn|Ogi|Suter|Lent|2019|p=248}}\n*Newcomer Award at the first Sino-Japanese Youth Exchange Cartoon Festival{{sfn|Ogi|Suter|Lent|2019|p=248}}\n\n== Bibliography == \n* ''Winter Fairy Tale'' (2002)\n* {{cite book |ref=harv|last=Da|first=Xia ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}})| authorlink =Xia Da| title = \u56db\u6708\u7269\u8bed/: \u590f\u8fbe\u4f18\u79c0\u6f2b\u753b\u77ed\u7bc7\u96c6|trans-title=April Story|year=2004| publisher = \u7535\u5b50\u5de5\u4e1a\u51fa\u7248\u793e| isbn= 9787505398962|language=Chinese}} <small>- Total pages: 174 </small> \n* {{cite book |ref=harv|last=Da|first=Xia ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}})| authorlink =Xia Da| title =\u6e38\u56ed\u60ca\u68a6|trans-title=|year=2008| publisher = \u6e56\u5357\u5c11\u5e74\u513f\u7ae5\u51fa\u7248\u793e| isbn= 9787535838858|language=Chinese}} <small>- Total pages: 85 </small>  \n* ''Peony Pavilion'' (2008)\n* ''Zi Bu Yu'' #1\u20132 (2008)\n* ''Tonglei'' (2009)\n* ''Morning Star of Midland'' (2009)\n* {{cite book |ref=harv|last=Da|first=Xia ({{zh|s=\u590f\u8fbe|p=|t=}})| authorlink =Xia Da| title =\u54e5\u65af\u62c9\u4e