=November 14, 2019}}</ref> In [[Major League Baseball Most Valuable Player Award|AL MVP]] voting, Xander Bogaerts finished fifth, Mookie Betts eighth, Rafael Devers 12th, and J. D. Martinez was tied for 21st.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=SoxNotes |number=1195129302892843008 |title=Red Sox' 2019 AL MVP Finishes: |date=November 14, 2019 |accessdate=November 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nJackie Bradley Jr.'s over-the-wall catch of a [[Trey Mancini]] drive on May 8 was selected as number one on the list of [[MLB Network]]'s Top 100 Plays of 2019, while number two on the list was an over-the-wall catch by [[Stevie Wilkerson]] on a drive that Bradley hit on September 29 at Fenway Park.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/top-plays-of-2019-mlb-season |title=These are the top 100 plays of 2019 |first=Manny |last=Randhawa |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=November 18, 2019 |accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Farm system==\n{{See also|Minor League Baseball|Boston Red Sox minor league players}}\n\n{{MLB Farm System\n|level4=[[Triple-A (baseball)|AAA]]|team4=[[Pawtucket Red Sox]]|league4=[[International League]]|manager4=[[Billy McMillon]]\n|level5=[[Double-A (baseball)|AA]] |team5=[[Portland Sea Dogs]]|league5=[[Eastern League (baseball)|Eastern League]]|manager5=[[Joe Oliver (baseball)|Joe Oliver]]\n|level6=[[Class A-Advanced|A-Advanced]] |team6=[[Salem Red Sox]]|league6=[[Carolina League]]|manager6=[[Corey Wimberly]]\n|level7=[[Single-A (baseball)|A]]|team7=[[Greenville Drive]]|league7=[[South Atlantic League]]|manager7=Iggy Suarez\n|level8=[[Class A-Short Season|A-Short Season]]|team8=[[Lowell Spinners]]|league8=[[New York\u2013Penn League]]|manager8=[[Luke Montz]]\n|level9=[[Rookie League|Rookie]]|team9=[[Gulf Coast League Red Sox|GCL Red Sox]]|league9=[[Gulf Coast League]]|manager9=[[Tom Kotchman]]\n|level11=[[Rookie League|Rookie]]|team11=[[Dominican Summer League Red Sox|DSL Red Sox 1]]|league11=[[Dominican Summer League]]|manager11=Ozzie Chavez\n|level12=[[Rookie League|Rooki