 cash considerations) from the [[Baltimore Orioles]] in exchange for minor league position players Noelberth Romero and Elio Prado.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/orioles/bs-sp-orioles-cashner-trade-20190713-vxcyy7f7hbd3la3fa3zvehzdyy-story.html|title=Orioles trade Andrew Cashner to Red Sox for two prospects|newspaper=[[The Baltimore Sun]]|author=Nathan Ruiz|date=July 13, 2019|accessdate=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* July 15: [[Eduardo N\u00fa\u00f1ez]] was designated for assignment;<ref>{{cite tweet |user=PeteAbe |number=1150830712519610368 |title=Eduardo Nunez DFA'd by the Red Sox. |date=July 15, 2019 |accessdate=July 15, 2019}}</ref> he was released on July 20.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=ChrisCotillo |number=1152631113929646080 |title=Red Sox released Eduardo Nunez, so he\u2019s now free to sign anywhere |date=July 20, 2019 |accessdate=July 22, 2019}}</ref>\n* September 1: The team activated pitcher [[Jhoulys Chac\u00edn]] when rosters expanded; Chac\u00edn had been signed to a minor league contract on August 31,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/redsox/2019/09/01/red-sox-call-six-rosters-expand-for-september/AAVB7Wisz7pMLr5ISdGgiM/story.html |title=Red Sox call up six as rosters expand for September |first=Alex |last=Speier |website=[[The Boston Globe]] |url-access=limited |date=September 1, 2019 |accessdate=September 1, 2019}}</ref> after being released by the [[Milwaukee Brewers]] on August 26.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://m.brewers.mlb.com/roster/transactions/2019/08 |title=Brewers Roster & Staff \u2013 Transactions |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=August 2019 |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Amateur draft===\nBoston's top ten selections in the [[2019 Major League Baseball draft|2019 MLB draft]], which started on June 3, are listed below.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlb.com/draft/tracker/all/team/redsox |title=2019 Draft Tracker - Boston Red Sox |website=[[MLB.com]] |accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref> The team did not have a first-round pick, due to being more than $40 million over the [[Major League Baseball luxury tax|MLB luxury tax]] threshold.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2019/06/03/major-league-baseball-draft |title=Why the Red Sox don\u2019t have a 1st-round pick in tonight\u2019s MLB Draft |first=Andrew |last=Mahoney |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=June 3, 2019 |accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Round\n! scope=\"col\"| Pick\n! scope=\"col\"| Player\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n! scope=\"col\"| B/T\n! scope=\"col\"| Class\n! scope=\"col\"| School\n! scope=\"col\"| Signing date\n|-\n|2\n|43\n|Cameron Cannon\n|Shortstop\n|R/R\n|4YR JR\n|[[Arizona Wildcats baseball|Arizona]]\n|June 12, 2019<ref name=TransJune>{{cite web |url=http://m.redsox.mlb.com/roster/transactions/2019/06 |title=Red Sox Roster & Staff \u2013 Transactions |date=June 2019 |accessdate=June 19, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2\n|69\n|Matthew Lugo\n|Shortstop\n|R/R\n|HS SR\n|[[Carlos Beltr\u00e1n#Personal life|Carlos Beltr\u00e1n Baseball Academy]] ([[Puerto Rico|PR]])\n|June 19, 2019<ref name=TransJune/>\n|-\n|3\n|107\n|Ryan Zeferjahn\n|Pitcher\n|R/R\n|4YR JR\n|[[Kansas Jayhawks baseball|Kansas]]\n|June 12, 2019<ref name=TransJune/>\n|-\n|4\n|137\n|Noah Song\n|Pitcher\n|R/R\n|4YR SR\n|[[Navy Midshipmen baseball|Navy]]\n|July 6, 2019<ref name=TransJuly/>\n|-\n|5\n|167\n|Jaxx Groshans\n|Catcher\n|R/R\n|4YR JR\n|[[Kansas Jayhawks baseball|Kansas]]\n|June 12, 2019<ref name=TransJune/>\n|-\n|6\n|197\n|Chris Murphy\n|Pitcher\n|L/L\n|4YR SR\n|[[San Diego Toreros baseball|University of San Diego]]\n|June 12, 2019<ref name=TransJune/>\n|-\n|7\n|227\n|Brock Bell\n|Pitcher\n|R/R\n|JC J3\n|[[State College of Florida, Manatee\u2013Sarasota]]\n|June 12, 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=http://soxprospects.com/players/bell-brock.htm |title=Brock Bell |website=soxprospects.com |accessdate=July 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|8\n|257\n|