rew Benintendi, and Christian Vazquez were also finalists for [[Rawlings Gold Glove Award]]s.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/redsox/2019/10/24/four-red-sox-named-gold-glove-finalists/zHL70ekP8jWHdQ2By3WaPO/story.html |title=Four Red Sox named Gold Glove finalists |first=Julian |last=McWilliams |website=[[The Boston Globe]] |url-access=limited |date=October 24, 2019 |accessdate=October 26, 2019}}</ref> [[Eduardo Rodr\u00edguez (left-handed pitcher)|Eduardo Rodr\u00edguez]] finished sixth in [[Cy Young Award]] voting.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/redsox/2019/11/13/gmmeets/V62Hrw2473eAwvrrOLTx1H/story.html |title=Eduardo Rodriguez, sixth in AL CY Young voting, didn\u2019t reach his own lofty goal |first=Alex |last=Speier |website=[[The Boston Globe]] |url-access=limited |date=November 13, 2019 |accessdate=November 14, 2019}}</ref> In [[Major League Baseball Most Valuable Player Award|AL MVP]] voting, Xander Bogaerts finished fifth, Mookie Betts eighth, Rafael Devers 12th, and J. D. Martinez was tied for 21st.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=SoxNotes |number=1195129302892843008 |title=Red Sox' 2019 AL MVP Finishes: |date=November 14, 2019 |accessdate=November 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nJackie Bradley Jr.'s over-the-wall catch of a [[Trey Mancini]] drive on May 8 was selected as number one on the list of [[MLB Network]]'s Top 100 Plays of 2019, while number two on the list was an over-the-wall catch by [[Stevie Wilkerson]] on a drive that Bradley hit on September 29 at Fenway Park.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/top-plays-of-2019-mlb-season |title=These are the top 100 plays of 2019 |first=Manny |last=Randhawa |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=November 18, 2019 |accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Farm system==\n{{See also|Minor League Baseball|Boston Red Sox minor league players}}\n\n{{MLB Farm System\n|level4=[[Triple-A (baseball)|AAA]]|team4=[[Pawtucket Red Sox]]|league4=[[International League]]|manager4=[[Billy McMillo